keyFacts: The subpoena is part of the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)).
It demands all records from January 1, 2008 to the present for aircraft with tail numbers N750A or N722JE.
The subpoena is issued to Insured Aircraft Title Service, LLC, an aircraft title service company based in Oklahoma City.
Failure to comply constitutes contempt of court with potential civil sanctions and criminal penalties.
